Reasoning: The paper proposes a research strategy for creating and deploying prescriptive recommendations for spreadsheet practice, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed scoping survey aims to gather empirical data on spreadsheet usage, which could be analyzed using database (cs.DB) techniques. The paper also mentions the importance of documenting existing standards for creation and use of spreadsheets, which could be relevant to the cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories.
